# Layout templates (from `layouts.json`)

Summarizes **171** files under **`**/layouts/**`** (see [`.agents/file-lists/layouts.json`](../file-lists/layouts.json)). Layouts compose **slots** (header/body/footer) and page chrome; often paired with **`.module.scss`**.

## Inventory snapshot

| Fact | Typical value |
| --- | --- |
| Extensions | `.tsx` (~53%), `.scss` (~44%), small `.js` / `.ts` |
| Path depth (median) | 9 segments |
| Common roots | `app/pages` (~75%), `app/features` (~14%), `app/components` (~10%) |
| Largest slice | `app/pages/Result/...` (~66%) |

**Path examples:**

- `app/layouts/OverlayLayout.tsx`
- `app/pages/Result/layouts/ResultTabsLayout.tsx`
- `app/pages/Result/features/TariffsOverview/components/TariffTile/features/TariffHints/layouts/TariffHintsLayout.module.scss`

## Role

- **Layout** = structural wrapper (grid, overlay chrome, tab shell), often **default export** function returning **`ReactElement`**.
- **Feature components** vs layouts: layouts focus on **composition** and **named slots** (`components` prop bag, render props, or children).

## Template — slot-based overlay

```typescript
import type { ReactElement } from "react";
import { renderIfNotNull } from "utils/renderIfNotNull";

interface Props {
  readonly components: {
    readonly header?: ReactElement;
    readonly body?: ReactElement;
    readonly footer?: ReactElement;
  };
}

export default function ExampleOverlayLayout(props: Props): ReactElement {
  return (
    <div>
      {renderIfNotNull(props.components.header, (header) => (
        <header>{header}</header>
      ))}
      {renderIfNotNull(props.components.body, (body) => (
        <main>{body}</main>
      ))}
      {renderIfNotNull(props.components.footer, (footer) => (
        <footer>{footer}</footer>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Styling

- Co-locate **`LayoutName.module.scss`**; use **BEM** block names matching the layout (**`rules-typescript-clean-code.mdc`**).

